# Writing Better Component APIs

A component API is a promise. It tells other developers what the component is for, what can change, and what should stay stable.

## What I like to avoid

- inputs that overlap in meaning
- outputs that are too generic
- components that depend on invisible layout assumptions

## A better default

```ts
@Input() loading = false;
@Input() disabled = false;
@Output() submitted = new EventEmitter<void>();
```

Even plain inputs like these reduce ambiguity. Most of the time the clearest API wins over the most flexible one.

## Why it matters

Good APIs do not just help consumers. They make future maintenance calmer because intent stays visible in the template and in tests.
